caregivers come and go. The Childs living in the street and in the =
orphanage doesn=E2=80=99t get chance to lead a comfortable life like a =
child who lived with his family. The life of Childs living in orphanage =
lead a life on the basis of a particular schedule, children get up, get =
cleaned, eat, learn, and regimented way. There is serious lacking of =
creativity in their lives. If you closely analyses their life style then =
you can realize more or less they are leading a life of robot that =
function on the basis of certain fixed programs. These children also =
have full right to lead a normal life like other children. But due to =
large in number and presence of fewer caretakers they are enabling to =
lead a fairytale life like others.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'margin-bottom:10.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:115%'>India =
is one of the most populous country where every day almost 34 Childs =
born and among them a large number of child are orphan. According to a =
study conducted by the Hindustan times there are 20million children =
those who are orphan, it occupy almost 4% of the total population of the =
nation. Not every child gets a chance to live with a family. Many more =
have to stay in an orphanage. Due to the large amount of number every =
child rising in the orphanage doesn=E2=80=99t get a chance to lead a =
happy life. More or less they are happy that they are getting chance to =
have food and have a place to sleep. But is this their destiny. No, this =
is not. We should take necessary steps to make their lives happier and =
interesting. Drawing and painting is a very nice way to develop the =
creativity and is better option to express ourselves. Children=E2=80=99s =
have an emotional attachment to painting and drawing. Even though =
painting is not every child=E2=80=99s cup of tea but every child should =
get a chance to draw and paint. Painting can help the child to =
communicate their emotions without the use of any words. It also allows =
children an educational opportunity which is very exciting, it helps in =
developing various types of skills among them; it is a great field to =
develop their creativity. Painting can play the role of therapy for a =
child who might be feeling different emotions; whether these feelings =
are subtle or extreme in nature. In addition to communication, painting =
can help children feel better about things that may have bottled up =
inside. It is a better way for expressing the innovative ideas.<span =
style=3D'font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Calibri",sans-ser=
if'><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'text-align:justify'>Children are the backbone of a nation and =
development of any nation depends on the health and well-being of its =
child population. India has the second largest child populations in the =
World. Child development encompasses the ways in which children acquire =
skills in a range of domains, including memory, cognition and language, =
gross and finer motor ability, social interaction and behavior. The =
first few years of life, especially infancy is a dynamic phase of life =
and is characterized by rapid growth and development. When children do =
not get the right start, they never catch up or reach their full =
potentials. Children are the essential part of the nation and they =
should be treated with much care, love and affection so that they can =
prosper to the fullest. People of the society should come forward to =
help these children by donating more and more product so that get full =
access to grow as well as to develop. These children are the future our =
nation and it=E2=80=99s on us how we are constructing our future. If we =
nurture them we love and provide them with books, color books and =
dresses then only these children get ample chance to grow =
individually.<span =
